webpackJsonp([85981566840613],{793:function(a,e){a.exports={data:{markdownRemark:{html:'<p>Program metrics show how healthy a program is. They enable hackers to see various statistics regarding:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Program information</li>\n<li><a href="#response">Response efficiency</a></li>\n<li><a href="#program">Program statistics</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The metrics are displayed on the right side of the program\'s security page.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/program-metrics-1-aa6bd2e36007a0cd7234d1e40682429a-1490b.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 500px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 74.36440677966102%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Program metrics"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/program-metrics-1-aa6bd2e36007a0cd7234d1e40682429a-2f183.png"\n        srcset="/static/program-metrics-1-aa6bd2e36007a0cd7234d1e40682429a-67829.png 125w,\n/static/program-metrics-1-aa6bd2e36007a0cd7234d1e40682429a-5c59f.png 250w,\n/static/program-metrics-1-aa6bd2e36007a0cd7234d1e40682429a-2f183.png 500w,\n/static/program-metrics-1-aa6bd2e36007a0cd7234d1e40682429a-c93e8.png 750w,\n/static/program-metrics-1-aa6bd2e36007a0cd7234d1e40682429a-4e628.png 1000w,\n/static/program-metrics-1-aa6bd2e36007a0cd7234d1e40682429a-b3ac4.png 1500w,\n/static/program-metrics-1-aa6bd2e36007a0cd7234d1e40682429a-1490b.png 1888w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h3>Displaying Program Metrics</h3>\n<p>To display program metrics on your security page:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to <strong>Program Settings > Program > Customization > Metrics Display</strong>.</li>\n<li>Select the statistics you want to display on your security page.</li>\n<li>Click <strong>Update</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-link"\n    href="/static/program-metrics-2a-074c364abd8dd06c82db9b8a5ec062d3-ac62f.png"\n    style="display: block"\n    target="_blank"\n    rel="noopener"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class="gatsby-resp-image-wrapper"\n    style="position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 500px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"\n  >\n    <span\n      class="gatsby-resp-image-background-image"\n      style="padding-bottom: 81.60442600276625%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(\'data:image/png;base64,\'); background-size: cover; display: block;"\n    >\n      <img\n        class="gatsby-resp-image-image"\n        style="width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;"\n        alt="Program metrics-2"\n        title=""\n        src="/static/program-metrics-2a-074c364abd8dd06c82db9b8a5ec062d3-2f183.png"\n        srcset="/static/program-metrics-2a-074c364abd8dd06c82db9b8a5ec062d3-67829.png 125w,\n/static/program-metrics-2a-074c364abd8dd06c82db9b8a5ec062d3-5c59f.png 250w,\n/static/program-metrics-2a-074c364abd8dd06c82db9b8a5ec062d3-2f183.png 500w,\n/static/program-metrics-2a-074c364abd8dd06c82db9b8a5ec062d3-c93e8.png 750w,\n/static/program-metrics-2a-074c364abd8dd06c82db9b8a5ec062d3-4e628.png 1000w,\n/static/program-metrics-2a-074c364abd8dd06c82db9b8a5ec062d3-ac62f.png 1446w"\n        sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h3 id="response">Response Efficiency Metrics</h3>\n<p>Response efficiency metrics include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Average time to first response</li>\n<li>Average time to triage</li>\n<li>Average time to resolution</li>\n<li>Average time to bounty</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The averages are calculated by the last 90 days. These metrics give hackers a better idea of how responsive a program is. Learn more about <a href="response-target-metrics.html">response efficiency metrics</a>.</p>\n<h3 id="program">Program Statistics</h3>\n<p>Program statistics are calculated over a programâ€™s lifetime. They set realistic expectations with hackers and security teams for how active your program is. Within the program statistics section of your security page, hackers can view:</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Item</th>\n<th>Details</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Total bounties paid</td>\n<td>Total bounties paid can be a strong indicator that a bounty program is active and healthy.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Average bounty</td>\n<td>The average bounty serves as rough guidance for how much a hacker can expect in return for a valid report. It\'s displayed as a range from the 45th to 55th percentile.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Top bounty range</td>\n<td>Displayed as a range from the 90th to 100th percentile.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Reports resolved</td>\n<td>The total number of valid reports that have been resolved.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Hackers thanked</td>\n<td>The total number of hackers that have submitted valid reports.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<blockquote>\n<p><i>Note: Any reports filed by a security team\'s members will not be reflected in the metrics.</i></p>\n</blockquote>',frontmatter:{path:"/programs/program-metrics.html",id:"programs/program-metrics",title:"Program Metrics",description:null}}},pathContext:{}}}});
